----------------------Node.js notes----------------------

What is it?
It's a way to write web servers using all JavaScript
http://www.tutorialspoint.com/nodejs/
https://nodejs.org/en/
https://code.tutsplus.com/tutorials/nodejs-for-beginners--net-26314

Why use it?
Event-driven IO, non-blocking
JavaScript is naturally event-driven
https://www.toptal.com/nodejs/why-the-hell-would-i-use-node-js

Other web servers:
Apache HTTP Server
NGINX
Apache Tomcat
Lighttpd
https://opensource.com/business/16/8/top-5-open-source-web-servers

Good introduction site:
https://www.sitepoint.com/node-js-is-the-new-black/

----------------------Chrome V8 Notes----------------------

What is it?
V8 compiles and executes JavaScript source code, handles memory allocation for objects, and garbage collects objects it no longer needs. (From the site word-for-word)
https://developers.google.com/v8/

How is it related to Node.js?
It's the engine that Node.js runs on  